{
  "document_id": "prov-9",
  "title": "Proverbs 9",
  "type": "study-bible",
  "translation": "Oxford",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "She has slaughtered her animals, she has mixed her wine, she has also set her table."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-h1kj-4",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "2 : . Meat was a delicacy reserved for special occasions; see Gen 18.7–8; 43.16; 1 Sam 25.2–35. Wine was mixed with spices; see 9.5; Song 8.2.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 9
      },
      "verse_start": 2,
      "verse_end": 2
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "She has sent out her servant-girls, she calls from the highest places in the town,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-h1kj-5",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "3 : , see 8.2n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 9
      },
      "verse_start": 3,
      "verse_end": 3
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "“You that are simple, turn in here!” To those without sense she says,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-h1kj-6",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "4 : , see 1.4n.; 1.22.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 9
      },
      "verse_start": 4,
      "verse_end": 4
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "“Come, eat of my bread and drink of the wine I have mixed."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-h1kj-7",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "5 : is described as an impediment one can choose to discard, see 1.22n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 9
      },
      "verse_start": 5,
      "verse_end": 5
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "Lay aside immaturity, and live, and walk in the way of insight.”"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-h1kj-2",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "9.1–6: Wisdom's house and invitation. To build a house(hold) is a mark of wisdom, see 14.1n.; 24.3.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 9
      },
      "verse_start": 1,
      "verse_end": 6
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "Whoever corrects a scoffer wins abuse; whoever rebukes the wicked gets hurt."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "A scoffer who is rebuked will only hate you; the wise, when rebuked, will love you."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-h1kj-9",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "7–8 : , see 1.22n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 9
      },
      "verse_start": 7,
      "verse_end": 8
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "Give instruction to the wise, and they will become wiser still; teach the righteous and they will gain in learning."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "The fear of the Lord is the beginning of wisdom, and the knowledge of the Holy One is insight."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-h1kj-10",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "10 : Reiteration of the book's motto; see 1.7n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 9
      },
      "verse_start": 10,
      "verse_end": 10
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "For by me your days will be multiplied, and years will be added to your life."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-h1kj-11",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "11 : , first-person-singular speech suggests that this is a misplaced conclusion to wisdom's invitation (vv. 1–6; cf. 8.15–16). , see 3.2n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 9
      },
      "verse_start": 11,
      "verse_end": 11
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "If you are wise, you are wise for yourself; if you scoff, you alone will bear it."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-h1kj-8",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "9.7–12: Counsel for teachers.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 9
      },
      "verse_start": 7,
      "verse_end": 12
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "The foolish woman is loud; she is ignorant and knows nothing."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "She sits at the door of her house, on a seat at the high places of the town,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-h1kj-13",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "14 : , see 8.2n. She and Wisdom are in many of the same places; see v. 3.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 9
      },
      "verse_start": 14,
      "verse_end": 14
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "calling to those who pass by, who are going straight on their way,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "“You who are simple, turn in here!” And to those without sense she says,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-h1kj-14",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "16 : The first line of her invitation is identical to Wisdom's (v. 4). S , see 1.4n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 9
      },
      "verse_start": 16,
      "verse_end": 16
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "“Stolen water is sweet, and bread eaten in secret is pleasant.”"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-h1kj-15",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "17 : , a metaphor for a woman who is engaged or married to another man; see 5.15–23n. Eating and drinking are metaphors for sex (cf. 7.18; 30.20; Song 5.1).",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 9
      },
      "verse_start": 17,
      "verse_end": 17
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "But they do not know that the dead are there, that her guests are in the depths of Sheol."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-h1kj-1",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "1.1–9.18: The proverbs of Solomon son of David, king of Israel.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 9
      },
      "verse_start": 1,
      "verse_end": 18
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-h1kj-12",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "9.13–18: Folly's house and invitation.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 9
      },
      "verse_start": 13,
      "verse_end": 18
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-9-h1kj-16",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "18 : , see 2.18n. , see 1.12n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 9
      },
      "verse_start": 18,
      "verse_end": 18
    }
  ]
}